FBIS4-6774 "dreas079_c_94003" FBIS-EAS-94-079 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 North Korea Radio Calls Perry's Trip to ROK `Criminal Act' Radio Calls Perry's Trip to ROK `Criminal Act' SK2204135694 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 22 Apr 94 SK2204135694 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 1300 GMT 22 Apr 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to reports from Seoul, U.S. Defense Secretary Perry made a junket [haenggak] to South Korea from 19 to 21 April. Perry's junket to South Korea was a junket of war to examine, on the spot, how their plan of a war of Northward aggression had been carried out and give new instructions to the puppets. During the junket, Perry met with traitor Kim Yong-sam, puppet Defense Minister Yi Pyong-tae, and puppet Foreign Minister Han Sung-chu respectively, held one military confab [kunsajok moui] after another, mapped out vicious plans [hyunggye] to resume the Team Spirit joint military exercise before the end of this year, build up the U.S.-South Korea combined forces, strengthen the cooperation system, and pursue the UN Security Council sanctions [jeje] against the North. This is an unforgivable criminal act to bring the situation on the Korean peninsula to a crisis phase and cause a very dangerous situation.
